1. Na pijaci su cene *paprika* veće nego prošle nedelje. (At the market, the prices of *peppers* are higher than last week.)
2. Prošle godine su se cene kuća *dramatično* povećale. (Last year, house prices *dramatically* increased.)
3. U ovoj prodavnici su cene *najniže* u gradu. (In this store, the prices are the *lowest* in town.)
4. Nisam siguran koliko koštaju ove cipele, ali se nadam da su *pristupačne*. (I'm not sure how much these shoes cost, but I hope they are *affordable*.)
5. U restoranu su cene jela *visoke*, ali je hrana ukusna. (The prices of the dishes in the restaurant are *high*, but the food is delicious.)
6. Svi su bili iznenađeni *sniženjem cena* tokom novogodišnjih praznika. (Everyone was surprised by the *price reductions* during the New Year holidays.)
7. Žalim što moram da vas obavestim da su cene *porasle* zbog nedostatka sirovina. (I regret to inform you that the prices have *risen* due to the lack of raw materials.)
8. Kupila sam novu torbu po *priličnoj* ceni. (I bought a new bag at a *reasonable* price.)
9. *Cene benzina* su se povećale poslednjih nedelja. (The *price of gasoline* has increased in recent weeks.)
10. Prodavnica je organizovala *rasprodaju* i sada su cene proizvoda *snižene* za 50%. (The store has organized a *sale* and now the prices of the products are *reduced* by 50%.)